headlines.description: — For a team that scuffled this season on the road, the Oklahoma City Thunder sure did look like a playoff team in Philly.
— No Kevin Durant on one side, no Jaylen Brown on the other.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics pull away in 4th, beat Nets 109-98 for 5th straight

headlines.description: — The Miami Heat were short-handed. The Milwaukee Bucks were short-handed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed Heat rally, top short-handed Bucks, 108-102

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 35 points, Scottie Barnes added 21 and the Toronto Raptors have won three consecutive games for the first time this season, beating the Charlotte Hornets 124-114 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 35, Raptors beat Hornets for 3rd straight win

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic hit tying 3-pointers in the final seconds of regulation and the first overtime, finishing with 35 points, 14 rebounds and 13 assists in the Dallas Mavericks' 119-115 double-overtime victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic hits 2 big 3-pointers, Mavs top Lakers 119-115 in 2OT

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 26 points, Ricky Rubio played in his first game since a knee injury more than a year ago and the Cleveland Cavaliers rallied in the fourth quarter to beat the Portland Trail Blazers 119-113 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rubio returns and Cavaliers down struggling Blazers 119-113
